description:
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Psychiatry, Eastbourne District General Hospital, East Sussex are looking for enthusiastic Bank Band 6 ODP to work with our dedicated team of professionals that provide the highest standards of care and support to people with acute mental health needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will have strong communication and people skills, a non-judgmental and person-centered approach and above all a real caring attitude and be prepared to make a difference. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return for your skills and expertise we can offer you continued training and development, variety and a rewarding challenge and the opportunity to work within friendly and supportive teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating Department Practitioner:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generally to assist the Anesthetist in delivering safe administration of the General Anesthetic in preparation for a service user receiving ECT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performs pre session checks and preparation of the emergency and resuscitation equipment, including all anesthetic equipment and oxygen supply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supports and assists the Anesthetist throughout the process of anesthetic induction from the point of contact with the service user to the full recovery of unassisted spontaneous respiration following anesthesia&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Michael Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title ECT Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address michael.nurse@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone numbe 01323 414943&lt;/p&gt;
